{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-a759d0e725786c20", "type": "tool_result", "content": "1\t<!DOCTYPE html>\n2\t<html lang=\"en\">\n3\t\n4\t<head><script>document.documentElement.classList.add('js');</script>  <title>[2607.12584v1] Explainable-by-Design Audio Deepfake Detection via Wiener-Hopf Linear Prediction</title>\n5\t  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n6\t  <link rel=\"apple-touch-icon\" sizes=\"180x180\" href=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/images/icons/apple-touch-icon.png\">\n7\t  <link rel=\"icon\" type=\"image/png\" sizes=\"32x32\" href=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/images/icons/favicon-32x32.png\">\n8\t  <link rel=\"icon\" type=\"image/png\" sizes=\"16x16\" href=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/images/icons/favicon-16x16.png\">\n9\t  <link rel=\"manifest\" href=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/images/icons/site.webmanifest\">\n10\t  <link rel=\"mask-icon\" href=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/images/icons/safari-pinned-tab.svg\" color=\"#5bbad5\">\n11\t  <meta name=\"msapplication-TileColor\" content=\"#da532c\">\n12\t  <meta name=\"theme-color\" content=\"#ffffff\">\n13\t  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"screen\" href=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/css/arXiv.css?v=20260318\" />\n14\t  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"print\" href=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/css/arXiv-print.css?v=20200611\" />\n15\t  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"screen\" href=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/css/browse_search.css\" />\n16\t  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"screen\" href=\"/static/base/1.0.1/css/arxiv-header-footer.css?v=20260626\" />\n17\t  <script language=\"javascript\" src=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/js/accordion.js\" ></script>\n18\t  <script language=\"javascript\" src=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/js/optin-modal.js?v=20250819\"></script>\n19\t  \n20\t  <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.12584\"/>\n21\t  <meta name=\"description\" content=\"Abstract page for arXiv paper 2607.12584v1: Explainable-by-Design Audio Deepfake Detection via Wiener-Hopf Linear Prediction\"><meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"website\" />\n22\t<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"arXiv.org\" />\n23\t<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Explainable-by-Design Audio Deepfake Detection via Wiener-Hopf Linear Prediction\" />\n24\t<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.12584v1\" />\n25\t<meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/images/arxiv-logo-fb.png\" />\n26\t<meta property=\"og:image:secure_url\" content=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/images/arxiv-logo-fb.png\" />\n27\t<meta property=\"og:image:width\" content=\"1200\" />\n28\t<meta property=\"og:image:height\" content=\"700\" />\n29\t<meta property=\"og:image:alt\" content=\"arXiv logo\"/>\n30\t<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"The rapid advancement of synthetic speech generation methods has made audio deepfake detection a critical challenge in multimedia forensics. While recent approaches achieve high detection accuracy, they typically rely on black-box architectures that offer limited interpretability and high computational complexity. In this paper, we propose an explainable-by-design audio deepfake detection framework based on Wiener-Hopf linear prediction, processed by a lightweight 2D Convolutional Neural Network (CNN). This design enables a direct and transparent connection between classification outcomes and the acoustic properties of the signal. Experimental results on benchmark datasets demonstrate competitive detection performance while maintaining significantly lower computational complexity compared to state-of-the-art solutions. The interpretability analysis using Grad-CAM reveals that the classifier focuses on low-order predictor coefficients and on silence and transitional regions, suggesting that the Wiener-Hopf predictor captures reverberation characteristics and subtle statistical inconsistencies in synthetic speech. Finally, robustness experiments show that fine-tuning effectively recovers detection performance under common post-processing degradations, including additive noise, MP3 compression, and telephone filtering.\"/>\n31\t<meta name=\"twitter:site\" content=\"@arxiv\"/>\n32\t<meta name=\"twitter:card\" content=\"summary\"/>\n33\t<meta name=\"twitter:title\" content=\"Explainable-by-Design Audio Deepfake Detection via Wiener-Hopf...\"/>\n34\t<meta name=\"twitter:description\" content=\"The rapid advancement of synthetic speech generation methods has made audio deepfake detection a critical challenge in multimedia forensics. While recent approaches achieve high detection...\"/>\n35\t<meta name=\"twitter:image\" content=\"https://static.arxiv.org/icons/twitter/arxiv-logo-twitter-square.png\"/>\n36\t<meta name=\"twitter:image:alt\" content=\"arXiv logo\"/>\n37\t  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"screen\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/css/tooltip.css\"/><link rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"screen\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"https://static.arxiv.org/js/bibex-dev/bibex.css?20200709\"/>  <script src=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/js/mathjaxToggle.min.js\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script>  <script src=\"//code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.min.js\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script>\n38\t  <script src=\"//cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/js-cookie@2/src/js.cookie.min.js\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script>\n39\t  <script src=\"//cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/dompurify@2.3.5/dist/purify.min.js\"></script>\n40\t  <script src=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/js/toggle-labs.js?20241022\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script>\n41\t  <script src=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/js/cite.js\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script><meta name=\"citation_title\" content=\"Explainable-by-Design Audio Deepfake Detection via Wiener-Hopf Linear Prediction\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Tamiazzo, Mattia\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Milani, Simone\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Iuliani, Massimo\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Fontani, Marco\" /><meta name=\"citation_doi\" content=\"10.1145/3785353.3815087\" /><meta name=\"citation_date\" content=\"2026/07/14\" /><meta name=\"citation_online_date\" content=\"2026/07/14\" /><meta name=\"citation_pdf_url\" content=\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2607.12584\" /><meta name=\"citation_arxiv_id\" content=\"2607.12584\" /><meta name=\"citation_abstract\" content=\"The rapid advancement of synthetic speech generation methods has made audio deepfake detection a critical challenge in multimedia forensics. While recent approaches achieve high detection accuracy, they typically rely on black-box architectures that offer limited interpretability and high computational complexity. In this paper, we propose an explainable-by-design audio deepfake detection framework based on Wiener-Hopf linear prediction, processed by a lightweight 2D Convolutional Neural Network (CNN). This design enables a direct and transparent connection between classification outcomes and the acoustic properties of the signal. Experimental results on benchmark datasets demonstrate competitive detection performance while maintaining significantly lower computational complexity compared to state-of-the-art solutions. The interpretability analysis using Grad-CAM reveals that the classifier focuses on low-order predictor coefficients and on silence and transitional regions, suggesting that the Wiener-Hopf predictor captures reverberation characteristics and subtle statistical inconsistencies in synthetic speech. Finally, robustness experiments show that fine-tuning effectively recovers detection performance under common post-processing degradations, including additive noise, MP3 compression, and telephone filtering.\" />\n42\t</head>\n43\t\n44\t<body ><div class=\"flex-wrap-footer\">\n45\t    <a href=\"#content\" class=\"ds-skip-link\">Skip to main content</a>\n46\t  \n47\t  \n48\t  \n49\t<header class=\"ds-site-header\">\n50\t  <a aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/IgnoreMe\" class=\"is-sr-only\"></a>\n51\t\n52\t  <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/\" class=\"ds-site-header-logo\" aria-label=\"archive home\">\n53\t    <img src=\"/static/base/1.0.1/images/arxiv-logo-primary-light.svg\" alt=\"archive\">\n54\t  </a>\n55\t\n56\t  <button type=\"button\" id=\"ds-nav-toggle\" class=\"ds-site-header-nav-toggle\"\n57\t    aria-label=\"Open menu\" aria-controls=\"ds-site-header-nav\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n58\t    <svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\">\n59\t      <line x1=\"3\" y1=\"6\" x2=\"21\" y2=\"6\"/>\n60\t      <line x1=\"3\" y1=\"12\" x2=\"21\" y2=\"12\"/>\n61\t      <line x1=\"3\" y1=\"18\" x2=\"21\" y2=\"18\"/>\n62\t    </svg>\n63\t  </button>\n64\t\n65\t  <nav class=\"ds-site-header-nav\" id=\"ds-site-header-nav\" aria-label=\"Main navigation\"><a id=\"arxiv-search-toggle\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/search\"\n66\t      aria-controls=\"arxiv-search-overlay\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n67\t      <svg class=\"ds-nav-icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\">\n68\t        <circle cx=\"11\" cy=\"11\" r=\"8\"/>\n69\t        <line x1=\"21\" y1=\"21\" x2=\"16.65\" y2=\"16.65\"/>\n70\t      </svg>\n71\t      Search\n72\t    </a>\n73\t    <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/user/create\">Submit</a>\n74\t    <a href=\"https://info.arxiv.org/about/donate.html\">Donate</a>\n75\t    <span class=\"ds-site-header-divider\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n76\t      <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/login\" class=\"ds-site-header-login\">Log in</a>\n77\t  </nav>\n78\t</header>\n79\t\n80\t<div class=\"arxiv-search-overlay\" id=\"arxiv-search-overlay\" hidden>\n81\t  <div class=\"arxiv-search-panel\" role=\"search\">\n82\t    <form method=\"GET\" action=\"https://arxiv.org/search\">\n83\t      <label for=\"arxiv-search-input\" class=\"is-sr-only\">Search arXiv</label>\n84\t      <input type=\"text\" name=\"query\" id=\"arxiv-search-input\" autocomplete=\"off\"\n85\t        placeholder=\"Search papers by title, author, abstract, or ID...\">\n86\t      <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"searchtype\" value=\"all\">\n87\t      <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"source\" value=\"header\">\n88\t    </form>\n89\t    <div class=\"arxiv-search-hint\">\n90\t      Press Enter to search &middot; <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/advanced\">Advanced search</a>\n91\t    </div>\n92\t  </div>\n93\t</div>\n94\t    <main>\n95\t      <div id=\"content\">\n96\t<!--\n97\trdf:RDF xmlns:rdf=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#\"\n98\t         xmlns:dc=\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\"\n99\t         xmlns:trackback=\"http://madskills.com/public/xml/rss/module/trackback/\">\n100\t    <rdf:Description\n101\t        rdf:about=\"/abs/2607.12584\"\n102\t        dc:identifier=\"/abs/2607.12584\"\n103\t        dc:title=\"Explainable-by-Design Audio Deepfake Detection via Wiener-Hopf Linear Prediction\"\n104\t        trackback:ping=\"/trackback/2607.12584\" />\n105\t    </rdf:RDF>\n106\t--><div id=\"abs-outer\">\n107\t\n108\t  <div class=\"leftcolumn\">\n109\t    <div class=\"subheader\">\n110\t      <h1>Computer Science > Sound</h1>\n111\t    </div>\n112\t\n113\t    <div class=\"header-breadcrumbs-mobile\">\n114\t      <strong>arXiv:2607.12584v1</strong> (cs)\n115\t    </div>\n116\t<link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"/static/base/1.0.1/css/abs.css\">\n117\t<div id=\"content-inner\">\n118\t  <div id=\"abs\">\n119\t    <div class=\"dateline\">\n120\t  [Submitted on 14 Jul 2026]</div>\n121\t    <h1 class=\"title mathjax\"><span class=\"descriptor\">Title:</span>Explainable-by-Design Audio Deepfake Detection via Wiener-Hopf Linear Prediction</h1>\n122\t    <div class=\"authors\"><span class=\"descriptor\">Authors:</span><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Tamiazzo,+M\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mattia Tamiazzo</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Milani,+S\" rel=\"nofollow\">Simone Milani</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Iuliani,+M\" rel=\"nofollow\">Massimo Iuliani</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Fontani,+M\" rel=\"nofollow\">Marco Fontani</a></div>            <div id=\"download-button-info\" hidden>View a PDF of the paper titled Explainable-by-Design Audio Deepfake Detection via Wiener-Hopf Linear Prediction, by Mattia Tamiazzo and Simone Milani and Massimo Iuliani and Marco Fontani</div>\n123\t    <a class=\"mobile-submission-download\" href=\"/pdf/2607.12584v1\">View PDF</a>\n124\t    <a class=\"mobile-submission-download\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/html/2607.12584v1\">HTML (experimental)</a>\n125\t\n126\t\n127\t\n128\t    <blockquote class=\"abstract mathjax\">\n129\t            <span class=\"descriptor\">Abstract:</span>The rapid advancement of synthetic speech generation methods has made audio deepfake detection a critical challenge in multimedia forensics. While recent approaches achieve high detection accuracy, they typically rely on black-box architectures that offer limited interpretability and high computational complexity. In this paper, we propose an explainable-by-design audio deepfake detection framework based on Wiener-Hopf linear prediction, processed by a lightweight 2D Convolutional Neural Network (CNN). This design enables a direct and transparent connection between classification outcomes and the acoustic properties of the signal. Experimental results on benchmark datasets demonstrate competitive detection performance while maintaining significantly lower computational complexity compared to state-of-the-art solutions. The interpretability analysis using Grad-CAM reveals that the classifier focuses on low-order predictor coefficients and on silence and transitional regions, suggesting that the Wiener-Hopf predictor captures reverberation characteristics and subtle statistical inconsistencies in synthetic speech. Finally, robustness experiments show that fine-tuning effectively recovers detection performance under common post-processing degradations, including additive noise, MP3 compression, and telephone filtering.\n130\t    </blockquote>\n131\t\n132\t    <!--CONTEXT-->\n133\t    <div class=\"metatable\">\n134\t      <table summary=\"Additional metadata\">        <tr>\n135\t          <td class=\"tablecell label\">Comments:</td>\n136\t          <td class=\"tablecell comments mathjax\">Accepted at ACM IH&amp;MMSec 2026</td>\n137\t        </tr>\n138\t<tr>\n139\t          <td class=\"tablecell label\">Subjects:</td>\n140\t          <td class=\"tablecell subjects\">\n141\t            <span class=\"primary-subject\">Sound (cs.SD)</span>; Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI); Cryptography and Security (cs.CR); Multimedia (cs.MM)</td>\n142\t        </tr><tr>\n143\t          <td class=\"tablecell label\">Cite as:</td>\n144\t          <td class=\"tablecell arxivid\"><span class=\"arxivid\"><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.12584\">arXiv:2607.12584</a> [cs.SD]</span></td>\n145\t        </tr>\n146\t        <tr>\n147\t          <td class=\"tablecell label\">&nbsp;</td>\n148\t          <td class=\"tablecell arxividv\">(or <span class=\"arxivid\">\n149\t              <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.12584v1\">arXiv:2607.12584v1</a> [cs.SD]</span> for this version)\n150\t          </td>\n151\t        </tr>\n152\t        <tr>\n153\t          <td class=\"tablecell label\">&nbsp;</td>\n154\t          <td class=\"tablecell arxivdoi\">              <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2607.12584\" id=\"arxiv-doi-link\">https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2607.12584</a><div class=\"button-and-tooltip\">\n155\t              <button class=\"more-info\" aria-describedby=\"more-info-desc-1\">\n156\t                <svg height=\"15\" role